After talking with Andrew who used to maintain the old stock craft repository i have decided to start us up a new one to get all those beautiful craft people are building in 0.25 shared amongst the people.

In this thread you will find a repository of all sorts of different stock crafts created by different people. To have your craft added here, make a post with a picture of your craft, a brief description (plus if it's for the VAB or SPH), and a download link.

Some good free uploading sites that will allow you to upload files are Google Drive, Dropbox, or MediaFire. If you don't want to make an account with a file sharing site, then use Wikisend to allow you to share your file for up to 90 days before it is deleted. Be sure to click "Properties" before you upload and set the lifetime to 90 days, or it will default to 7.

For image hosting, Imgur works best with the KSP forums and allows you to create albums which you can embed in your posts. If you don't want to create an account, use PostImage. It will host your images forever.

There are two rules for submitting crafts:

- They must be compatible with the latest version of KSP. (v0.25)

- They must be completely stock.

Vehicle Assembly Building

Rockets with Payloads - Rockets that deliver stuff to low (or high) orbits around Kerbin. Not to be confused with subassemblies

Payloads by Themselves - Some payloads lack lifters, and those go here.

Orbital Stations - These may or may not include lifters.

Mun/Minmus Crafts - Crafts that can orbit around or land on one of Kerbin's moons

Bases - Base modules and base packs, with or without rockets, go here.

Interplanetary Crafts - Crafts designed to go to other planets, but not necessarily return.

Other - Crafts that don't fit the above categories.

Space Plane Hanger

Kerbin SSTOs - A plane which uses a combination of jets and rockets (or RAPIERs) to reach orbit around Kerbin, but not beyond.

I will get the ball rolling with my SR-71 B-2 Spirit bomber and SR-72.

SR-71 white bird

Description: Not made with FAR or NEAR.

I have decided to start building replica planes and where better to start than the SR-71?

This replica is capable of 25km flight like the original at over 3500km/h, it is stable at any fuel level and quite maneuverable for what it is (I did my best on the flying capabilities)

Download link:

http://www./download/kzxsdkb3tkasa16/Sr-71+white+bird.craft

SR-72 White bird

Description: Not made with FAR or NEAR.

After finishing the SR71 and B-2 Spirit bomber i set my eyes on the experimental SR-72 and i am very happy with the results of my labour, capable of over 8600kmh at 35km in the atmosphere this plane is a true high altitude sub orbital flyer, but do not be fooled by its high altitude speed, at low altitudes this plane is very maneuverable and completely stable with SAS never being required (unless you are lazy)

As an added bonus feel free to deplete the fuel and never have to worry about the centre of mass moving to a place that will cause instability in the plane.

Have fun and enjoy this craft.

I do not believe i need to leave any form of flight instructions for this plane.

Download link:

SR-72 White bird, Part count 254.

http://www./download/krai8x2hcbmfwbr/SR-72+White+bird.craft

B-2 Spirit bomber

Description: Not made with FAR or NEAR.

After the first b-2 i made soulreaver gave some helpful pointers on how i could get the plane to look more authentic and then i decided to improve on the originals performace because why not? and i am 5 times happier than i was originally with the results.

It comes equipped with drop bombs in the bomb bay and is capable of 2100+m/s in the upper atmosphere.

Very stable and easy to take off/land, SAS is never required (unless doing some crazy things in the upper atmosphere)

I may have gone a tad over board you can nearly orbit it.... feel free to remove the clipped internals to decrease the performance.

Action groups:

1 toggle engines

2 toggle bay doors

Space bay releases 2 "bombs" at a time.

Download link: part count 373

http://www./download/50eg7zxadhp7xxj/B-2+Spirit+bomber+mk2.craft

Mind if I spam a whole bunch of replicas and some other 0.25 stuff?

Just asking because I don't know if this thread allows promoting stuff, as they already have their own thread (check my signature)

I started 0.25 off with a design binge, due to the new parts, which later spilled over to other things (see below). First up, some SSTOs:

Perdix

Simple SSTO using the new parts, comes in two variants, a crew version and a cargo version, which can take 2.5t to orbit, and have fuel to spare

Torai

It's sort of the nephew of the Perdix. I redesigned the wing shape for a smoother look, and a single turbojet means no flat spin on burn out

I also made a whole bunch of replicas in my 0.25 design binge, such as:

Orion

Features a more realistic CM than the standard Mk 1-2 pod, and with a crew capacity of 6 instead of the often seen 3. the download includes two launchers, Ares I and SLS

ATV

Carries a medium cargo of LFO to a station, using RCS propulsion. The leftover RCS can also be considered cargo. It launches on an Ariane 5, which leaves no debris in orbit.

Soyuz & Progress

Probably one of the most famous soviet craft out there. It comes in three flavours: the manned Soyuz, the unmanned Progress with RCS cargo, and one with Life Support (mod can be found here). The launcher itself can lift up to 6 tons, and is, along with the Progress fairing, included as subassemblies.

The Proton Pack

The pride of my replica fleet, and comes with several prebuilt payloads, such as Mir modules, OPSEK modules, Russian ISS modules, the TKS and the Salyut stations. It also has its own thread, instead of just the company thread in my sig, which you can find here

More pictures and info can be found on the thread in my sig, and the Proton thread. have fun

For your consideration (Space Shuttle category) :

Introducing the Osprey STR Mk I, the birth of a new era in reliable, performance oriented LKO-capable transportation technology.

Osprey STR Mk I is the shuttle for everyone! Launching as a rocket and landing as a plane, Osprey STR Mk I is a radically simplified, robust, 100% stock parts platform from the minds at SSL, and is double engineered to ensure superior flight stability, mission adaptability and ease of operation.

Equipped with powerful dual Toroidal Aerospike main engines, 4 Rockomax 24-77 OMS engines, 2 TurboJet atmospheric engines, a state of the art DTS-M1 communications package and a spacious cargo bay, Osprey STR Mk I is ideally suited for a wide range of low Kerbin orbit scientific and resupply missions.

Along with the complete STR platform, a standalone Osprey orbiter is included for training purposes.

* Action Group #1 toggles Toroidal Aerospike main engines

* Action Group #2 toggles Rockomax 24-77 OMS engines

* Action Group #3 toggles TurboJet atmospheric engines
